  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "UCB (User configuration Block) has very important configuration based on which Aurix chip acts. This wiki page explains how to update the BMHD in UCB binary"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "BMHD information"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_11-22-11.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_11-22-11.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Steps to update BMHD:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you update wrong information in BMHD and flash there is a high chance the board can go into unrecoverable error state (After which we need to erase using Memtool and miniwiggler)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Make sure the changes are updated in both Original and Copy of BMHD. As shown in below table, If BMHD0_ORIG is in Error state than firmware will check the BMHD0_COPY"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_11-33-44.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_11-33-44.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Repo path where the BMHD binary shall be placed: Project\\Config\\Autosar\\laut-tc3xx\\UCB\\BMHD"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Since we don't have any script to write the UCB, below is one of the workarounds to update BMHD"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 1:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Flash the current binary using Lauterbach Change the required value in Trace32 → Follow below steps"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Click on Check",
        "Click on edit",
        "Change the required value",
        "Click on update",
        "Check the BMI, CRCBMHD, CRCBMHD_N"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-6-57.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-6-57.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-7-17.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-7-17.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-7-31.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-7-31.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 2:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We can update UCB srec in two ways"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Dump the UCB block from Trace32 (Easy way)",
        "Change the existing UCB via HEX view or"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "1. Dump the UCB block from Trace32"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After updating the UCB in Trace32, Now dump the UCB into a file"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Data.save.IntelHex Dflash_ucb 0xAF402200–0xAF4023FF"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-2-13.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-2-13.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Now the UCB will be in the name of Dflash_ucb in Build folder"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Now open the UCB in hexview. We can see the start address is not correct."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-3-12.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-3-12.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Now double clock in start address and give the proper start address in new address"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-5-6.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2024-12-31_14-5-6.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After this start address will be ok and we can use this UCB hex file for project"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "2. Change the existing UCB via HEX view"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "UCB binary Path: Project\\Zeekr_May20\\Config\\Autosar\\laut-tc3xx\\UCB"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "BMHD binary path: Project\\Config\\Autosar\\laut-tc3xx\\UCB\\BMHD"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Make sure both UCB.SREC and BMHD (ORIG and COPY) binaries are modified"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Open the UCB from Repo in Hexview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below picture shows the mapping"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Now Edit the values in Hex view and save it (Make sure CRCBMHD and CRCBMHD_N is updated as well)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Careful on the Endianness"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Aurix%20-%20How%20to%20Update%20UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-8-34.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Aurix - How to Update UCB-BMHD/image-2023-5-22_13-8-34.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 3:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Flash the new UCB and make sure the data is updated properly in UCB Trace 32 window"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 4:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Deliver the BMHD binary to repo and inform all stakeholders"
    }
  ],
